        "content": "<p>(<span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"282271\">@Bolton Bailey</span> <code>nat.card</code> has been there for a while, but it's little by little seeing more use since you can avoid needing additional <code>fintype</code> and <code>decidable</code> instances, and especially the associated dependent type issues. Inside proofs there are ways to turn things into <code>fintype.card</code> if you need it. There's still API work into it and <code>finite</code> that's on pause due to the porting effort.)</p>",
        "id": 370573890,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1687986030
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Is it really gaining any traction? I've used it less and less.</p>",
